-- frontierism UI Library v1.0.0
-- Synapse X inspired theme, full bug-fix pass, performance improvements

--[[
	FIXES & IMPROVEMENTS OVER v0.0.3:
	[CRITICAL] ZV2 was never defined - crashed on drag init
	[CRITICAL] ColorPicker / Dropdown InputBegan close-listeners leaked on every open
	[CRITICAL] Blur stacked on every CreateWindow call (no cleanup guard)
	[CRITICAL] Notification Y-lerp read AbsoluteSize before first render (always 0)
	[CRITICAL] tabList CanvasSize was never set (tabs overflowed silently)
	[BUG] Tooltip RenderStepped lerp used clamp(dt*20) which overshoots at high FPS
	[BUG] Dropdown menu position is stale after page scroll (uses AbsolutePosition snapshot)
	[BUG] string.lower aliased as `slow` but used as `sfind` in one path
	[BUG] Slider dragging leaked uis.InputChanged / InputEnded connections globally
	[BUG] ColorPicker sliders shared same leaked global connections
	[BUG] Keybind widget rebuilt TextLabels every RenderStepped frame
	[PERF] All RenderStepped connections replaced with targeted task.spawn loops
	[PERF] TweenCache now weak-values so GC can collect completed tweens
	[DESIGN] Full Synapse X dark-blue aesthetic
	[DESIGN] Toggle redesigned as animated pill/switch
	[DESIGN] Slider redesigned with dot-thumb indicator
	[DESIGN] Better section labels with left accent bar
	[DESIGN] Dropdown and ColorPicker pop upward when near screen bottom
	[DESIGN] Notification stacking now uses AbsoluteContentSize for precise layout
	[NEW] AddSection() - visual divider with title
	[NEW] AddParagraph() - multiline read-only text element
	[NEW] Window:SetTheme() - swap full theme at runtime
	[NEW] Smooth window resize on minimize (height only, width preserved)
	[NEW] 2D Hue+Saturation canvas in color picker (proper Obsidian style)
]]

